<H1>Where Can I Buy Turtle-Safe Shrimp?</H1>

As of December, 1995 the following retailers and restaurants had offered Turtle-Safe shrimp to their customers.  Note that availability may vary due to fluctuations in supply.<P>

This list keeps growing as sea turtle activists contact more and more outlets.   Check out the action box to the left and get involved!

<H2>Some of the restaurants and markets where you can ask for Turtle-Safe shrimp:</H2>

<H3>San Francisco, CA area</H3>
Bryan's Quality Meats, San Francisco<P>
Chez Panisse, Berkeley<P>
Claremont Hotel, Oakland<P>
Culinary Institute of America at Greystone<P>
Hayes St. Grill, San Francisco<P>
Lark Creek Cafe, Walnut Creek<P>
Monterey Fish Market, North Berkeley<P>
Roti, San Francisco<P>
Square One, San Francisco <P>

<H3>Boston, MA</H3>
Bread & Circus markets (all eight stores!)

<H3>Hartford, CT</H3>
Cheese & Stuff Market

<H3>Colorado</H3>
Alfalfa's markets in Denver, Boulder, and Fort Collins<P>
Marina Landing Restaurant, Denver<P>
Mel's Bar & Grill, Denver

