<TITLE>Greek sea turtle activist bombed.</TITLE>

<H1>Greek sea turtle activist bombed.</H1>

Sea turtle activists on the Greek island of Zakynthos, who are fighting to
protect the Mediterranean's most important loggerhead sea turtle nesting beach,
have long been targeted by interests opposed to restrictions on tourism
development.  Activists have been shot at, beaten, had their offices set on
fire, and received telephone threats and verbal harasssment.<P>

On September 29, 1995, 3.3 pounds of dynamite exploded on the roof of the Sea
Turtle Protection Society of Greece (STPS) and Zakynthos Ecological Movement
(ZOK) office.  Fortunately none of the 15 ZOK staffers and three children who
were working on the organization's newsletter at the time were killed, although
architect Nikos Lykouresis, a founding member of ZOK, was wounded.<P>

STPS has gathered 51,000 signatures on a petition to the Greek government to
establish a National Marine Park on the island of Zakynthos.  Despite support
for the marine park from most Zakynthos residents, the local hoteliers' chamber
and the European Union (which has promised funding for the proposed park),
pro-development politicians continue to block protection of these critical
loggerhead sea turtle nesting beaches.<P>

<H2>Please speak out!</H2>

The international community must condemn these acts of violence!  YOU CAN HELP
by writing to:<P>

Konstantinos Laliotis<BR>
Minister of the Environment <BR>
Physical Planning and Public Works<BR>
Amaliados 17<BR>
115 21 Athens Greece<BR>
Fax 30-1-645-1793<P>

Please send copies of your letters to STPS, 35 Solomou Street, GR-106 82 Athens, Greece, tel/fax 01-3844-146.  <A HREF="mailto:sea turtle@igc.apc.orgs">Email us</A> if you would like a sample letter.


