<TITLE>~Archived STRP</TITLE>

<H1>~Archived STRP</H1>

<H2>STRP's philosophy</H2> The Director of the STRP, Todd Steiner states, <P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>"David <A HREF="../brower/browerbr.html">Brower</A>, founder of
Earth Island Institute, often speaks of 'peace on and with the earth.' To this
vision we would add - justice and respect for the environment and all people.
As an action-oriented group, we feel our values are best reflected by our work.
We are attempting to protect the ecological needs of endangered species while
meeting the needs of disenfranchised local people who themselves have been
exploited by a system that has profit as its only goal. We work closely with
and coordinate our international campaigns with the emerging environmental
movements in the countries where we work." </BLOCKQUOTE><P>

In addition to taking direct action on issues it perceives as critical, a goal
of the STRP is to be a catalyst for action by the larger environmental
community and a resource for information on sea turtle campaigns for various
organizations. The Project has an internship program that brings undergraduate
and graduate students, recent graduates and law students into the organization
to function as staff members. Individuals from Yale University, World College
West, Northern Arizona University, Colorado College, U.C. Santa Cruz, U.C.
Berkeley, U.C. San Diego, Pitzer College, and Golden Gate University School of
Law have all participated. The exchange of information and skills enhances the
work of the organization and is mutually educational to interns and staff
alike. STRP has also presented papers at professional meetings, has given
presentations at various schools in the San Francisco area, at universities and
at corporations in the region. <I>Ancient Sea Turtles: Their Last Voyage?</I>,
a video co-produced by STRP is distributed nationally to educational
institutions.<P>

STRP is the plaintiff in a major lawsuit aimed at international protection of
sea turtles and is being represented by the prominent San Francisco law firm of
Heller, Ehrman, White and McAuliffe. The firm is providing its services on a
<I>pro bono basis</I>.<P>



<A HREF="turtlesafe.html">Why should you ask for Turtle-Safe
shrimp?</A><P> <A HREF="strpca.html">Central American Nesting Beach
Program</A>.<P> <A HREF="strpexpd.html">Expedition program</A>.<P> <A
HREF="strpindi.html">India Campaign</A>.<P> <A
HREF="strplati.html">Latin American Monitoring</A>.<P> <A
HREF="strpprob.html">Statement of the Problem</A>.<P> <A
