<HEAD>

<TITLE>Brower Fund: CPR for the Earth</TITLE>

</HEAD>



<BODY>

<BODY BGCOLOR="ADEAEA">



<H1>CPR for the Earth</H1>



<BLOCKQUOTE>&quotDavid Brower has been for many years a steady force of nature, drawing 

us to see the natural world as nurturer, teacher, inspirer, and partner. [He has] been the 

pathbreaker, not given to easy answers or ruinous compromises...  A man of great insight 

who cares deeply for his world.&quot</BLOCKQUOTE>

--Former U.S. President Jimmy Carter<P>



David Brower is an elder of the environmental movement, and a visionary spokesman.  He 

has inspired countless wilderness advocates to dedicate their lives as stewards of the 

Earth.  David has a proven track record of being a non-compromising ally of the Earth, and 

his inspirational lectures challenge us to be bold leaders.  In his lifetime David has 

participated in some of our nation's greatest environmental battles.  &quotToo much of our 

work,&quot he opines &quotmearly slows the rate at which things are getting worse, we must invest 

ourselves and our time towards making things better.&quot  David fears we are a nation being 

eroded by its addiction to growth, living off natural resource capital, not just the interest.  

Despite many discouraging signs, Brower remains an optimist, intrigued by human potential.

<P>



<BLOCKQUOTE>&quotSo speed the healing of the planet we all share.  The cost of the Green 

Century is so essential that it warrants compulsory investment.  There will be a guaranteed 

return.  Failure to make that investment will cost far more than humanity and our fellow 

sentient beings can afford.&quot</BLOCKQUOTE>

--David Brower<P>



David Brower regularly travels across the country and overseas delivering his prescriptions 

for peace, on and with the Earth.  Now 83, David Brower draws on nearly sixty years of 

environmental activism to promote CPR for the Earth.  David Brower's CPR for the Earth 

lecture promotes planetary <STRONG>C</STRONG>onservation, 

<STRONG>P</STRONG>reservation and <STRONG>R</STRONG>estoration.  David 

argues that the combined use of these strategies will afford us a future by design, not by 

default.<P>



David regularly speaks to college audiences, government agencies, multi-national 

corporations and appears on national media programs and in publications.  He is particularly 

interested in reaching out to the younger generation, and to the business community to 

share his knowledge and to inspire change.  Few speakers can articulate the need for 

renewed hope in our common future than David Brower.<P>



Honoraria from David's speaking engagements help support fledgling environmental and 

social initiatives through the <A HREF="brower.html">Brower Fund</A> at 

<A HREF="../index.html">Earth Island Institute</A>.  By inviting David Brower to speak at 

your next conference, group meeting or festival you will take an important step towards 

committing yourself and others to the opportunities for a more ecologically sustainable, 

peaceful and just society.<P>



David is available to speak on a wide variety of issues, and is careful to acknowledge the 

specific concerns of the host group.  Past lecture topics include:  Land Conservation,  The 

Meaning of Wilderness to Science, On 50 Years of Environmental Activism, Overcoming 

Barriers to World Peace, and Economics of Sustainability.<P>



In the Past year David has delivered speeches to tens of thousands of people accross the 

country.  These lectures have included:  Patagonia Inc. (all company meeting), Interface 

(annual meeting), Sella Foundation (Italy), United States Environmental Protection Agency 

(twice), The Presidio Conference, The Windstar Foundation, The Charlie Rose program 

(national television), and dozens of others.<P>



Biographical materials, articles by and about David Brower are available by request.  David 

Brower's two-volume autobiography (<A HREF="brow1.html">For Earth's Sake</A>, and 

Work in Progress and his most recent publication 

<A HREF="brow3.html">Let the Mountains Talk, Let the Rivers Run</A> are available 

throught EII.<P>



<H3>Call Earth Island</H3>



To request a visit from David Brower for your next gathering call the Brower Fund at Earth 

Island Institute at USA 415-788-3666 X 112.<P>



