<HR><A NAME="other">
<H2>Organizations of some interest</H2>
These links represent in no way an endorsement by Earth Island:<P>

<A HREF="http://faraday.clas.virginia.edu/~djp2n/asle.html">ASLE</A>: The Association for the Study of Literature and Environment.<BR>
ASLE promotes the exchange of ideas and information pertaining
to literature that considers the relationship between human
beings and the natural world.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.emf.net/~cheetham/ken.html">Bay Area Progressive Calendar and Directory</A> by Ken Cheetham<P>

<A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/cnp">Campaign for New Priorities</A>: militarizing the US
budget<P>

<A HREF="http://www.cdt.org">Center for Democracy and Techology</A><BR>
Develops and advocates public policies that advance constitutional
civil liberties and democratic values in new computer and communications
technologies.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.earthpledge.org">Earth Pledge</A> a non-profit foundation,
recognizes appropriate intersections between business interests and
environmental, social, and cultural concerns.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.islandpress.com/Eco-Compass/ECOCOMPHOME.htm">Eco-Compass</A>: environmental web sites<P>

<A HREF="http://www.podi.com/ecosource/">Eco-Source</A>: information for
ecotourism and other sustainable development issues<P>

<A HREF="http://ecosys.drdr.virginia.edu/EcoWeb.html">EcoWeb</A>: recycling, environmental
information and resources.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.eff.org">Electronic Frontier Foundation</A><BR>
Working in the public interest to protect privacy, free expression, and access
to online resources and information.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.ratical.com/corporations/">Ending Corporate Governance</A> is a information resource to
assist in redefining the subordinate nature of these legal
ficticious entities in relation to flesh-and-blood people.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.ozemail.com.au/~tropical/index.html">The Far North
Queensland Almanac</A>: The people, the places and the environment of
Australia's Far North Queensland.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.foe.org/">Friends of the Earth</A> and <A
HREF="http://www.foe.org/rangewatch/rwindex.html">Range Watch</A><P>

<A HREF="http://www.greens.org/">Green Parties of North America</A><BR>Discover
the Green political movement, independent journalism, and alternatives to the
products of transnational corporations. Created by <A
HREF="http://www.rahul.net/cameron/">Cameron Spitzer</A><P>

<A HREF="http://www.princeton.edu/~mlevy">Global Environmental Policy Research Tools</A><BR>
Listings of institutes and think tanks, international collaboration, and information about governments<P>

<A HREF="http://hawaii-nation.org/nation/">Hawai`i</A>Independent & Sovereign<P>

The International Petition In Support of a Comprehensive <A
HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/NON-NUKE/">Test Ban Treaty</A> and Abolition
2000</A><P>

<A HREF="http://www.webcom.com/iwcwww/">International Wildlife Coalition</A><BR>
An advocate for wildlife,  established to prevent cruelty to wildlife, killing
of wildlife, and the destruction of wildife habitat.<P>

<A HREF="http://softcomm.com/mangrove/mangrove.htm">Mangrove Replenishment</A><P>

<A HREF="http://www.politicalindex.com">National Political Index</A>: substantive political information<P>

<A HREF="http://www.npr.org/">NPR</A>: National Public Radio<P>

<A HREF="http://www.sedona.net/nen/nhne">NewHeavenNewEarth:</A> A grass roots
network seeking to give birth to a new way of life on our planet.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.newparty.org/">The New Party</A>: from the webmaster: "Frankly, I don't know
much about this party, but it sounds interesting."<P>

<A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/lctr/">The Labor / Community Strategy Center</A> is a multiracial
anticorporate "think-tank/act-tank" committed to building
democratic internationalist social movements.<P>

<A HREF="http://edweb.sdsu.edu/edfirst/prophets/prophets.html">Nonprofit Prophets:</A>
High school students choose a social or environmental issue .  The
students create Web pages for non-profits.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.pacrivers.org/">Pacific Rivers Council</A>: one of the
largest and most successful river conservation organizations in the United
States.<P>

<A HREF="http://envirolink.org/arrs/peta/index.html">People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals</A>:
largest animal rights organization in the world<P>

<A HREF="http://www.planet.ark.com.au">Planet Ark</A>: environmental NetRadio news bulletin.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.pctvi.com/eco-active.html">Planet Central Television</A>: A
conscious television network, with shows on ecology, alternative health,
spirit, art and human rights.<P>

<A HREF="http://censored.sonoma.edu/ProjectCensored/">Project Censored</A><BR>
Explores and publicizes the extent of censorship in our society by locating
stories about significant issues of which the public should be aware, but is
not.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.sfc.keio.ac.jp/~s93073no/site.html">Sites</A> for <A HREF="../strp/strpindx.html">turtles, tortoises</a> and terrapins!!!<P>

<A HREF="http://www.sfgate.com/userpages/spj/index.html">Society of Professional Journalists</A>, northern California chapter<P>

<A HREF="http://www.tpl.org/tpl">The Trust for Public Land</A>: (TPL) is a
national, nonprofit land conservation organization that conserves land for
people to enjoy as parks, gardens, natural areas and open space.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.io.org/~bunrab/">Turtle Trax</A>: A page devoted to Marine Turtles.<P>

Karil Daniels' <A HREF="http://www.well.com/user/karil">Waterbirth website</A>:
safe, gentle, joyous childbirth.<P>

<A HREF="http://whales.magna.com.au/home.html">Whales on the Net</A><P>

<A HREF="http://www.honors.indiana.edu/~veggie/recipes.cgi">Veggies Unite!</A> is a on-line guide to vegetarianism.<P>

<HR><A NAME="companies">
<H2>Companies</H2>
These links represent in no way an endorsement by Earth Island:<P>


<A HREF="http://www.discovery.com">Discovery Channel Online</A><P>

<A HREF="http://www.dolphin-synergy.com/">Dolphin-Synergy</A>: DanielMcCulloch is considered one of the foremost Dolphin photographers.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.ecoemporium.com">Eco Emporium</A> sells earth-friendly products<P>

<A HREF="http://www.ecomall.com">EcoMall: </A>"A place to help save the Earth"
 Daily Eco News - Activism - Companies Products, Eco Links - Eco Quotes...<P>

