<TITLE>Wishlist</TITLE>

<H1>Wishlist</H1>

<H2>Help us help you</H2>

Earth Island Institute is mostly Macintosh based, even though some projects such as 
<A HREF="../gsc/gschome.html">Global Service Corps</A> and 
<A HREF="../baikal/baikal.html">Baikal Watch</A> use PC's.
If your not sure what you've got, give you can contact <A HREF="mailto:kenyarb@earthisland.org">Ken Yarborough</A>.<P>

<H2>Macintosh</H2>

For Mac's, we'd one of these: "II" series, LC, Performa, Quadra, Centris or PowerPC (gulp!). Powerbooks
or Duos would be fantastic too.<P>

<H2>PC</H2>

For PC's, we'd prefer 486 or Pentium (gasp!) PC's or laptops.<P>

<H2>Other stuff</H2>

If you want to help get more of Earth Island on the "information super-highway," we need modems that
are 9600 baud or better (14.4 or 28.8 would be great!)<P>

<H2>Experts or Interns</H2>
Minimum 4 hours per week, not tax-deductible<P>

<UL>

<LI>Media/ PR

<LI>Planned-giving Law

<LI>WWW design

<LI>Reception

</UL>

<H2> How to reach us</H2>

If your not sure what computer stuff you've got, give you can contact Ken Yarborough  in one of three ways:

<OL>

<LI>email: <A HREF="mailto:kenyarb@earthisland.org">kenyarb@earthisland.org</A><P>

<LI>415-788-3666 X 121 anytime<P>

<LI>snail mail:<BR>
Earth Island Institute<BR>
300 Broadway #28<BR>
San Francisco CA 94133<BR>
USA<BR>

</OL>

