<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Welcome to the Southern Rockies Restoration Project</TITLE><H2><B><CENTER>The Southern Rockies Restoration Project</CENTER></B></H2><!-- Graphic Tag --><H1><IMG SRC="neversummer.gif" WIDTH="261" HEIGHT="176" VSPACE=12 HSPACE=12
ALIGN=left BR CLEAR=left NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="0"></H1> <BR><BR>


<BODY>

The Southern Rockies Restoration Project is a nonprofit organization
dedicated to the rehabilitation of damaged lands in the Southern Rockies
Ecoregion through the establishment of citizen-based watershed councils, and
the design and implementation of watershed restoration plans.  SRRP is a
project of <A HREF="../index.html">Earth Island Institute</A>, an
international environmental consortium founded in 1982 by veteran
environmentalist David Brower.</P>

<BR CLEAR=ALL><BR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><BLOCKQUOTE><CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="overview.html">Project Overview</A> | <!-- Link Tag --><!--A HREF="region.html">The Southern Rockies Ecoregion</A></CENTER>
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><!--A HREF="assess.html">Regional Watershed Assessment</A> | <!-- Link Tag --><!--A HREF="councils.html">Watershed Councils</A></CENTER>
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="adopt.html">Adopt-A-Watershed</A></CENTER>
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><!--A HREF="councils.html">Join the Southern Rockies Restoration Project</A></CENTER></BLOCKQUOTE></P>
<BR>

<BR>

For more information about SRRP and how you can help us restore the health of the Southern Rockies Ecoregion, <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:srrp@cris.com">email us!</A>
<P>
