<TITLE>Baikal Watch</TITLE>
<H1>Baikal Watch</H1>
<IMG ALIGN=top SRC="baikalmp.gif"><P>

It's not too late to expand your summer horizons, and spend <A HREF="050196.html">
three full weeks under the warm SIBERIAN sun!</A><P>

Dedicated to the preservation of Lake Baikal and the Siberian frontier. Please
check out our <A HREF="fall95.html">Baikal Currents</A>-- Issue #2, Fall
1995</A>. <P>

<BLOCKQUOTE><I>This huge, old, beautiful lake, 
surrounded by wildness, is a 
<A HREF="baikal2.html">world treasure, a world heritage</A>. 
But right now the world needs to 
come to Lake Baikal's <A HREF="baikal1.html">rescue</A>.
</I></BLOCKQUOTE>
<A HREF="../brower/browerbr.html">David Brower</A><P>


See <A HREF="fall95.html">Baikal Currents- Fall 1995</A>: The Informational Bulletin of the <A HREF="bcci.html">Baikal Center for Ecological and Citizen Initiatives</A>.<P>


Baikal  Watch... 

<UL>

<LI>  was formed to assure the permanent  
    protection of Lake Baikal and its  
    surroundings, and to <A HREF="baikal1.html">restore the 
    environmental</A> integrity of the <A HREF="baikal2.html">lake and
    its watershed</A>.<P>

<LI>  spearheads programs to help strengthen the 
    system of national parks and nature reserves 
    in Siberia and gain World Heritage Site status 
    for the <A HREF="baikal2.html">lake and its environs</A>.<P>

<LI> coordinates international efforts at developing 
    eco-tourism in the parks and reserves in 
    Siberia and the Baikal region.<P>

<LI>  organizes international exchange programs 
    for training Russian specialists in issues such 
    as <A HREF="baikal1.html">environmental</A> law and protected area 
    management.<P>

<LI> offers technical and financial assistance and 
    donates vital equipment to Russian environmentalists, scientists, and governmental 
    institutions working to save Baikal.<P>

<LI> serves as a clearinghouse for information 
    about Baikal and Russia, and facilitates several
    collaborative projects and expeditions with   
    other groups working in the former USSR.<P>

</UL>

