<TITLE>Stewards of the Earth (SE)</TITLE>
<H1>Stewards of the Earth (SE)</H1>

Stewards of the Earth (SE) is based in Goleta, California, on a century-old organic farm surrounded by urban development, which supplies local residents with nearly 100 different varieties of fruits and vegetables through a community supported agriculture program and retail store.  SE conducts educational activities about food and agriculture, including:  tours and live-in programs for school classes; lecture programs and concerts; "from the field to the plate" cooking classes; horticultural therapy for individuals with physical and developmental disabilities; and training programs for at-risk youth in Santa Barbara and Los Angeles counties.  SE has produced <I>From the Good Earth, A Celebration of Growing Food Around the World</I>, an illustrated book, as well as multi-media slide show, traveling exhibition, and public lectures dealing with food and agricultural issues across five continents. The project is developing an organic agricultural training program for inner city youth from the Los Angeles area which will culminate in an installation of an urban organic farm in that area.  Project Director: Michael Ableman. <P>

