<TITLE>EINS: Other Organizations and Web sites</TITLE> 
<H1>Other Web Sites</H1>

<A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org"><IMG SRC="at.igc.gif" Border=0 ALIGN=RIGHT></A>

Did you try to <A HREF="/scripts/wwwwais/config=ei">search</A> our pages? What
your looking for may be in the <A
HREF="../journal/journal.html">Journal</A>. May we also strongly recommend <A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/">The Progressive Directory @IGC</A>.<P>

<P>

<HR>
These home pages and organizations are not directly related to EII and some organizations do not have Internet addresses.<P>
This growing list was designed so that viewers can, using most Browsers, search for key words such as "human rights", "Green Plans", or "environmental justice" to locate a particular listing.<P>
<LI>Organizations <A HREF="otherweb.html#wwwgrp">with WWW sites</A> working to protect the Earth<P>
<LI>Organizations <A HREF="otherweb.html#nowwwgrp">without WWW sites</A> working to protect the Earth<P>
<LI>Organizations <A HREF="otherweb.html#other">of some interest</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="otherweb.html#companies">Companies</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="otherweb.html#tools">Tools to Search for Information</A><P>
<LI><A HREF="otherweb.html#news">Publications and News Services </A><P>
</UL>

<HR><A NAME="wwwgrp">

<H2>Organizations with WWW sites</H2>

<B>Earth Island's opinionated list of strong advocates for the Earth:</B><P>

<A HREF="http://www.afseee.org">Association of Forest Service Employees for Environmental Ethics (AFSEEE)</A><BR>
PO Box 11615<BR>
Eugene, OR 97440<BR>
tel:(503)484-2692<BR>
fax: (503) 484-3004<BR>
E-mail: afseee@afseee.org.<BR>
Seeks the preservation of ecological values and biological diversity in our national forests through educating and advocating for reforms of US forest service management practices.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.uky.edu/Agriculture/Forestry/AppalFor/aspi.html">Appalachia--Science in the Public Interest (ASPI)</A><BR>
Route 5, Box 423<BR>
Livingston, KY 40445<BR>
tel: (606) 453-2105<BR>
fax: (606) 453-3115<BR>
Organizes citizens to take control of their own lives and the region's natural resources.  It advocates simple living, which it views as a means of self determination.  Projects include the Rockcastle Resource Center, which demonstrates resource conservation and organic gardening; annual Simple Lifestyle Calendars; and a resource assessment service available to groups wanting to transform their properties into self-sustaining centers.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.cnt.org/">Center for Neighborhood Technology</A><BR>
2125 West North Avenue<BR>
Chicago, IL 60647<BR>
Phone: 312- 278-4800<BR>
Fax: 312-278-3840<BR>
E-mail: info@cnt.org<BR>
http://www.cnt.org/<BR>
Promotes public policies, new resources and accountable authority which support sustainable, just, and vital urban communities.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.ucsc.edu/costano/CulturalConservancy.html">Cultural Conservancy</A><BR>
Melissa K. Nelson, Executive Director<BR>
P.O. Box 72086<BR>
Davis, CA 95617-6086<BR>
Phone: 916-759-2285<BR>
Fax: 916-759-2268<BR>
E-mail: mknelson@igc.apc.org<BR>
http://www.ucsc.edu/costano/CulturalConservancy.html<BR>
Works with native people to protect important cultural and historical sites around the world.<P>

<A HREF="http://envirolink.org/orgs/ef/index.html">Earth First!</A><BR>
P.O. Box 1415<BR>
Eugene, OR 97440<BR>
Tel: (503) 741-9191<BR>
Fax: (503) 741-9192<BR>
E-mail: earthfirst@igc.apc.org<BR>
gopher://gopher.igc.apc.org/11/orgs/ef.journal<BR>
"No compromise in defense of Mother Earth." Direct action, deep ecology.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.igc.org/fair/">FAIR- Fairness & Accuracy In Reporting</A><BR>
130 W. 25th St.<BR>
New York, NY 10001<BR>
Tel: 212-633-6700<BR>
Fax: 212-727-7668<BR>
E-mail: fair@fair.org <BR>
http://www.igc.org/fair/<BR>
National media watch group
offering well-documented criticism in an effort to correct media bias and
imbalance. FAIR focusses public awareness on the narrow corporate
ownership of the press, the media's allegiance to official agendas and
their insensitivity to women, labor, people of color, and other public interest
constituencies.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.ilsr.org">Institute for Local Self-Reliance</A><BR>
Minnesota Office<BR>
1313 Fifth Street, SE, Suite 306<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55414-1546<BR>
Tel: (612) 379-3815<BR>
Fax: (612) 379-3920<BR>
E-mail: jbailey@great-lakes.net<BR>
Works to develop a sustainable society by building strong, democratic, sef-reliant communities that can efficiently utilize local natural, social, and economic resources.<P>


<A HREF="http://www.irn.org/">International Rivers Network</A><BR>
1847 Berkeley Way<BR>
Berkeley CA  94703<BR>
Phone: 510/848-1155.<BR>
E-mail: irn@igc.apc.org<BR>
Researches and publishes information concerning threats to rivers, watersheds, and local populations from destructive development projects. Supports grassroots water projects in the Third World.Concerned with multilateral development banks and the social and environmental impact of their projects.<P> 

<A HREF="http://www.panna.org/panna/">Pesticide Action Network</A><BR>
North America Regional Center<BR>
116 New Montgomery St. #810<BR>
San Francisco, CA 94105<BR>
Tel: (415) 541-9140<BR>
Fax: (415) 541-9253<BR>
E-mail: panna@panna.apc.org<BR>
International coalition of citizen's groups and individuals who advocate adoption of ecologically sound practices in place of pesticide use.<P>


<A HREF="http://www.ran.org/ran/">Rainforest Action Network</A> (former project of Earth Island).<BR>
Randy Hayes, Executive Director<BR>
450 Sansome, Suite 700<BR>
San Francisco, CA 94111<BR>
Phone: 415-398-4404<BR>
Fax: 415-398-2732<BR>
E-mail: rainforest@ran.org<BR>
http://www.ran.org/ran/<BR>
Works to protect rainforests,indigenous peoples' human rights, and land rights in tropical countries; endangered species protection.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.rri.org/whats-rri.html">Resource Renewal Institute</A><BR>
Huey D. Johnson, President<BR>
Fort Mason Center- Building A<BR>
San Francisco, CA 94123<BR>
(415)928-3774<BR>
E-mail: info@rri.org<BR>
http://www.rri.org/<BR>
Promotes Green Plans as the path to a sustainable environment and economy.  Green Plans are dynamic programs by which all elements of society agree on long-term environmental goals and take responsibility for achieving them.<P>

<A HREF="http://solstice.crest.org/efficiency/rmi/index.html">Rocky Mountain Institute</A><BR>
1739 Snowmass Creek Rd.<BR>
Snowmass, Colorado 81654<BR>
Phone: 970-927-3851<BR>
E-mail: orders@rmi.org<BR>
http://solstice.crest.org/rmi<BR>
Rocky Mountain Institute is a nonprofit research and educational foundation with a vision across boundaries. Its mission is to foster the efficient and sustainable use of resources as a path to global security.<P>

<A HREF="http://www.well.net/mwec/wer.html">Whole Earth Review</A><BR>
Whole Earth Review Customer Service<BR>
P.O. Box 3000<BR>
Denville, NJ 07834<BR>
Phone: 1-800-783-4903<BR>
Fax: 415-332-3110<BR>
E-mail:wer@well.com<BR>
http://www.well.net/mwec/wer.html<BR>
A quarterly magazine produced by the Point Foundation. <CITE>WER</CITE> is an ongoing supplement to the <CITE>Whole Earth Catalog</CITE>, a resource book of tools & ideas contributing towards a sustainable future that "includes all cultures & communities."<P>

<A HREF="http://www.wald.com">Working Assets Long
Distance</A><BR>
701 Montgomery Street #400<BR>
San Francisco, CA 94111<BR>
Phone: 1-800-788-0898<BR>
Fax: 415-788-7572<BR>
E-mail: wald@wald.com<BR>
http://www.wald.com<BR>
For profit company with long distance service and visa cards that works for social change.  Gives portion of profits to various environmental groups, as well as pro-choice and human rights organizations and informs its customers about important campaigns and issues. <P>

<HR><A NAME="nowwwgrp">

<H2>Organizations without WWW sites</H2>

<B>Earth Island's opinionated list of strong advocates for the Earth:</B><P>

Cenozoic Society<BR>
Wild Earth<BR>
P.O. Box 455<BR>
Richmond, VT 05477<BR>
tel: 802-434-4077<BR>
Publishes the conservation quarterly Wild Earth. Wild Earth advocates the restoration and protection of all natural elements of biodiversity, serves ecocentric grassroots groups within the conservation movement.<P>

Centre de Documentation et de Recherche sur la Paix et les Conflits (CDRPC: Documentation and Research Center on Peace and Conflicts)<BR>
BP 1027, 69201 Lyon Cedex 01, France<BR>
tel: (33 for France) 78 36 93 03<BR>
