<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE>Tree-Free Fibers</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="denim.gif" LINK="#75480a" VLINK="#015800">

<H1>&nbsp;</H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="image6.gif" WIDTH="168" HEIGHT="36" ALIGN="TOP"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="2" BORDER="2"></H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><BR>
Tree-Free Fibers</H1>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <P><FONT SIZE=+1>The US Department of Agriculture has spent 40 years investigating
  more than 500 plants to find the best fiber for pulping paper. While hemp
  has historically been the most recognized plant for tree-free paper, the
  USDA has identified another plant, kenaf, as the most viable fiber to produce
  tree-free paper.<BR>
  <BR>
  There are numerous agrifibers ideally suited for paper production, including
  kenaf, hemp, agricultural residues (cereal straws, cotton linters, etc.),
  and reclaimed fabric. Most of these agrifibers yield more pulp-per-acre
  than forests or tree-farms, and require fewer pesticides and herbicides.
  In addition, fewer chemicals and less time and energy are needed to pulp
  and bleach agricultural fibers. In fact, agrifibers can be effectively
  brightened using totally-chlorine-free (TCF) bleaching processes, thus
  eliminating the production of highly toxic chlorine byproducts (such as
  dioxin) commonly associated with paper production. Crops such as hemp and
  kenaf also provide a means of adding strength to recycled fibers without
  using wood. </FONT></P>
  <P><BR>
  <HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>
  <H3 ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="scoop.gif" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="43" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></H3>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="rtp.html">ReThink Paper Home Page</A> <BR>
    <A HREF="overview.html">Campaign Overview</A> | <A HREF="ffpcamp.html">The
    main components of ReThink Paper</A> <BR>
    <A HREF="sus.paper.html">The Sustainable Paper Cycle: A Vision for the
    future</A> <BR>
    The Plain Pulp Facts: <A HREF="paperstats1.html">Volume 1</A> | <A HREF=
    "woodfact.html">Wood Consumption Facts </A><BR>
    <A HREF="tfpdef.html">Tree-free fibers and paper </A>| <A HREF="ecosources.html">Ecological
    paper suppliers and resources </A><BR>
    Tree-free fibers for papermaking: <A HREF="kenaf.html">Kenaf</A>; <A HREF=
    "hemp.html">Hemp</A> <BR>
    <A HREF="wycd.html">What you can do to &quot;ReThink Paper&quot;</A> |
    <A HREF="eiiffpp.html">Earth Island Journal</A></P>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
