<head>



<title>Joshua Bruce Bio</title>



</head>







<H2><center>Joshua Bruce -- New GSC Latin America Program Coordinator</center></H2>







<body>







<BR> 







Global Service Corps is pleased to welcome Joshua Bruce as our new Latin America Program Coordinator.  



After completing a semester internship with GSC this past  December, Joshua returned to Humboldt State 



University (California) where he is completing his B.A. in Recreational Administration, with a concentration 



in community service. In January, Joshua visited the New Forests Project training center in Guatemala and 



met with the center coordinator, Leonel Jarquin.  During this time, initial planning took place for our new 



Guatemala project.  Joshua will be returning to Costa Rica to lead our June, August and December trips 



and will also lead the first Guatemala project trip in October.<p>







Joshua brings to his new position with Global Service Corps a wealth of experience in Latin America and 



outdoor education.  He spent his junior year in high school in Brazil where he became fluent in Portuguese 



and has since developed a proficiency in Spanish.  An avid outdoorsman, Joshua has lead a variety of 



outdoor training programs and is an experienced white water rafter.  He is also certified as an Emergency 



Medical Technician. Joshua is a fun-loving and well organized trip leader as well as a committed 



environmentalist and community servant.  He has already made a number of close friends in our host



communities in Costa Rica and Guatemala and they are looking forward to his return.  We are pleased to 



have him as part of the GSC team.<p>







