<TITLE>Ocean Alert Fall 1995: A Message from David Phillips</TITLE>

<H1>A Message from David Phillips</H1>

<IMG SRC="immp14-2.gif" ALIGN=Left 
VSPACE=10
HSPACE=10>

One thing is clear in this line of work -- our victories are never permanent. The political 
climate in Washington, DC these days has put a number of our hard-fought 
environmental-protection laws at risk.
<P>

Under the guise of "deregulation," bills have been introduced to gut the Endangered 
Species Act, the Clean Water Act, and the Marine Mammal Protection Act. The impact on 
the dolphins and whales you and I have fought so hard for -- and on endangered rhinos, 
tigers, and other species; on the air we breathe; the water we depend on for life; and the 
health of the entire Earth -- can't yet be measured.
<P>

Countries like Japan and Norway are watching with keen interest to see whether US 
leadership on wildlife protection can be undermined. They are poised to resume extensive 
commercial whaling if they can get away with it.
<P>

Foreign governments, such as Mexico and Venezuela, and even some former US tunaboat 
owners, are taking aim at dolphins again. They are trying to allow dolphin-unsafe tuna back 
on supermarket shelves and to permit a return to the bad old days when US tuna vessels 
killed tens of thousands of dolphins every year. Congressional hearings are taking place on 
proposals to dismantle the entire US dolphin-safe policy.
<P>

We've come too far to let this happen now. Dolphin mortality in the Eastern Tropical Pacific 
Ocean has been reduced by more than 96 percent as a result of the dolphin-safe campaign. 
Consumers support it, the tuna companies support it -- it is a major success story, but we 
must remain ever vigilant to keep the oceans safe for dolphins.
<P>

In the coming months, we will need your help to block those who would destroy our 
environmental protection laws. It won't be easy, but together we must hold on to the 
progress we've made and continue our push to make the oceans safe for all species.
<P>

<BR>

<A HREF="oasf95.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="arrowrt.gif">Ocean Alert - Summer/Fall 1995</A>.<P>

<A HREF="immp.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="arrowrt.gif">IMMP table of contents</A>.<P>

