<TITLE>Ocean Alert Fall 1995: Monitor Highlight</TITLE>

<H1>Monitor Highlight</H1>

<IMG SRC="jacqline.gif" ALIGN=Right 
VSPACE=10 
HSPACE=10>

Jacqueline Sauzier is the regional coordinator of the EII-Mauritius monitoring program office. 
Since early 1994, Sauzier has been inspecting the tuna canneries and  ports of Mauritius to 
validate the dolphin-safe activities in the region. Sauzier is also a supporter of the Friends 
of the Environment and the Mauritius Marine Conservation Society, two non-governmental 
organizations in Mauritius.
<P>

Says Sauzier of her job with the monitoring program, "...working with Earth Island Institute 
made me discover international issues that are unknown in Mauritius. I have also learned a 
lot about the world of tuna fishing and canning." She continues, "I was able to meet Mr. 
Gome Gnohite Hilaire, the regional coordinator for the EII-Ivory Coast monitoring office ... I 
am glad to be a part of the Earth Island 'family'."
<P>

<BR>

<A HREF="oasf95.html"><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="arrowrt.gif">Ocean Alert - Summer/Fall 1995</A>.<P>

