<TITLE>Ocean Alert Fall 1995: What You Can Do</TITLE>

<H1>What You Can Do</H1>


<B>Take Action</B>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Only buy dolphin-safe tuna.
<P>
<LI>Don't buy Norwegian products, such as fish and cheese, until 
Norway stops whaling.
<P>  
<LI>Urge local supermarkets and restaurants to sell only EII-approved, dolphin-safe 
tuna and not to sell Norwegian products.
<P>
<LI>Ensure that your school cafeteria or workplace serves only EII- approved, 
dolphin-safe tuna.
<P>
<LI>Write to us if you would like the Life in the Sea Discovery Kit. Please include 
$3.00 for shipping. This education kit has all you need to create school units on dolphins, 
whales, and the marine ecosystem.
<P>
<LI>Start an environmental club at your school and organize local citizen-action 
groups in your community. Get involved!
<P>
</UL>
<P>

<IMG SRC="dolphin1.gif" ALIGN=Right 
VSPACE=10 
HSPACE=10>

<B>Voice Your Opinion</B>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Encourage local newspapers, radio, and TV stations to cover  tuna/dolphin and 
whaling issues.
<P>
<LI>Send letters to your senators and representatives encouraging them to take a 
strong position against commercial whaling. Also tell them to hold firm and not allow any 
weakening amendments to be added to the International Dolphin Conservation Law. 
<P>
<LI>Write letters to the editors of local newspapers and express your concern for 
marine mammals.
</UL>
<P>

<B>Write Letters</B>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>Write to Vice President Al Gore and urge that due to Norway's defiance of the 
IWC and sound science, that the US administration place sanctions on Norway's fish 
products. It is time for the US government to get tough!<BR> 
	The White House<BR>
	1600 Pennsylvania Avenue, NW<BR> 
	Washington, DC  20500
<P>

<LI>Write to Gro Harlem Brundtland, Prime Minister of Norway. Demand that Norway 
put an end to the senseless slaughter of whales.<BR> 
	Gro Harlem Brundtland<BR>
	Prime Minister of Norway<BR>
	Norwegian Embassy<BR>
	2720 34th Street, NW<BR>
	Washington, DC  20008
<P>

<LI>Write to the governor of Hawai'i and demand that the Humpback Whale Sanctuary 
be established there immediately.<BR> 
	Hawai'ian Governor Ben Cayetano<BR>
	Executive Chamber<BR>
	State Office Tower<BR>
	235 S. Beretania Street<BR>
	Honolulu, HI  96813
<P>

<LI>Write to the Pelagic Shark Research Foundation to learn more about its shark 
protection efforts.<BR>
	PSRF<BR>
	333 Lake Avenue, Suite H<BR>
	Maritime Center<BR>
	Santa Cruz, CA  95062
<P>
	
<LI>Write to the SF Bay Seal Project to get more information on becoming involved in 
the effort to protect harbor seals.<BR>
	Dianne Kopec<BR>
	PO Box 806<BR>
	Montara, CA  94037
<P>

<LI>Contact Whales Alive to learn more about its efforts to protect whales and how 
you can get involved in the work.<BR>
	Whales Alive<BR>  		
	PO Box 2058<BR>
	Kihei, HI  96753
<P>

<LI>Write to the Keiko project to receive updates about Keiko and the effort to 
rehabilitate him.<BR>
