<TITLE>Free Willy News: Special Thanks</TITLE>

<H1>Special Thanks.</H1>

Though many individuals deserve praise, here's a short list.

<IMG SRC="fw-kids.gif"  WIDTH=236 HEIGHT=165 ALIGN=RIGHT>

<H2>You!</H2>

The Free Willy - Keiko Foundation is grateful to the tens of thousands of people
who have contributed to our efforts to move Keiko to the Oregon Coast Aquarium
and begin his rehabilitation. The creativity and commitment schools and other
organizations have demonstrated for the cause are impressive.<P>

The initiative demonstrated by students throughout the country testifies to
children's concern for protecting wildlife and demonstrates their ability to make
a difference.<P>

Please write to us for more information about what you and your
school group can do to get involved!

<H2>Discovery Channel</H2>
Beginning on October 28th, the <A HREF="http://www.discovery.com/">Discovery
Channel</A> documentary, "The Keiko Story" began airing. The hour long program
is Executive Produced by ABC/Kane, and produced by Stan Minasian and Raymond
Chavez, and is the most comprehensive coverage of the Keiko's move and the
effort to prepare him for return to the wild.<P>

In the past, the Discovery
channel has broadcasted short updates on Keiko's progress hosted by
world-renowned whale expert Dr. Roger Payne.

<H2>Expert staff at the Oregon Coast Aquarium</H2>

Keiko's former trainers in Mexico City, Karla and Renata, are joined by four
expert staff at the Oregon Coast Aquarium to work on Keiko's health and
conditioning.

<H2>The Free Willy - Keiko Foundation</H2>

The Foundation is proud to welcome new President Beverlee Hughes. She has come
aboard on-site at our facility in Newport, Oregon, providing expert skills in
administration and oversight of the Foundation's activities.<P>

