<TITLE>Mitsubishi Alert: Vezcaino Desert Reserve Wildlife</TITLE>



<H1>Wildlife of the Vezcaino Desert Reserve</H1>



This fragile breeding and calving environment for gray whales is 

also home to many marine and terrestrial plant and animal species.  

<A HREF="../strp/strpprob.html">Sea turtles</A>, the endangered pronghorn antelope, mountain lions, 

coyotes, resident and migratory birds such as the peregrine 

falcon, golden eagle, black brant geese, osprey, and blue-wing 

teal all make their home there.  Scallop, clam, lobster and 

abalone fisheries sustain the resident community.  In the 

project's environmental impact statement(EIS)  ES claims no damage 

to the lagoon and surrounding area would take place because this 

site is "wastelands with little biodiversity and no known 

productive use."<P>



