<TITLE>IMMP: Agreement to stop eating Washington State fish.</Title>
<h2>Agreement to stop eating Washington State fish.</h2>
<I>Agreement to stop eating Washington State fish in response to sea lion kills and poor management of fishing runs.</I><P>



I, the undersigned, agree not to buy or consume any fish caught in Washington State waters if any sea lions are killed under the guise of improving fish runs. If sea lions are killed in Washington State, then a precedent will be set for the slaughter of marine mammals throughout the country. Fish populations are crashing worldwide because of human greed and mismanagement. Marine mammals should not be slaughtered because we have killed too many fish and ruined the environment. If there are not enough fish for the orcas, dolphins, seals, and sea lions in Washington State, then there are not enough for me. Marine mammals do not have a choice to eat anything but fish - but I do. Therefore, I agree to give up eating Washington fish so that I do not contribute to the death of our nation's marine mammals by competing with them for what little fish is left in our oceans and so that I do not support inhumane and unscientific fishing methods which involve the killing of marine mammals.<p>

Washington State Department of Fish and Wildlife and National Marine Fisheries Service are responsible for protecting both marine mammals and fisheries. If they do not do their job and protect both, then I will work toward that end myself. These agencies will be responsible for this action because they will force citizens to take measures to protect what the agencies have allowed to be destroyed. Marine mammals are a national treasure and we demand that they, as well as the fish, be protected and allowed to live. <P><P><P>

 __________________________________<BR>
 Signature<P>

 __________________________________<BR>
 Name (please print) <P> 

 __________________________________<BR>
 Address<P>

 __________________________________<BR>
 City, State, Zip<P>


<B>Please send this agreement
as soon as possible:</B><P>
Friends of Animals<BR>
P.O. Box 121<br>
Post Townsend, WA
98368
<BR><I>http://www.earthisland.org/immp/slpetition.html</I><BR>
