<TITLE>Baikal Currents-Informational Support, Publicity, and Citizen Networks</TITLE>

<H1>Informational Support, Publicity, and Citizen Networks</H1>

<H2>Baikal E-Mail Network Growing</H2>

For a organization descriptions, see p.13,17. Two more cities: Baikalsk and Severobaikalsk have access to this means of communication. New users are:<P>

<UL>

<LI>Severobaikalsk (davan@glas.apc.org)<P>

<UL>

<LI>Davan Club--E. Mariasov, D.Senotrusov<P>

<LI>Young Tourists Station--M.and M. Moshkin<P>

<LI>Young Naturalists Station--Natalya Schepina<P>

<LI>Sister-City Initiative Group--Maria Dubnova<P>

<LI>Ecopolis, an alternative housing--N. Yankovskii<P>

<LI>Young Journalists Club--F. Pilugin, an environmental journalist and reporter for the Buryat newspaper<P>

</UL>

<LI>Baikalsk (ceei@cetin.irkutsk)<P>

<UL>

