<H1>Ecotours To Baikal-Summer Of 1996.</H1>

<TITLE>Baikal Currents- Ecotours To Baikal-Summer Of 1996.</TITLE>

Consider a 3-week sojourn to the national parks and nature reserves that surround Lake Baikal

<UL> <LI>Fly to the Russian Far East via Alaska, spend 48 hours on the most scenic part of the trans-Siberian
railway, stay with Siberian families or at a special alternative medicine clinic in the heart of Tibetan
Buddhist Buryatia.<P>

<LI>Be pampered with massages, herbal baths, and quick but bracing dips into the Lake itself.<P>

<LI>Be entertained by local Buryat singing ensembles.<P>

<LI>Photograph the famous frolicking Baikal seals as they loll about on the shores of Baikal.<P>

</UL>

And be satisfied in the knowledge that you are supporting the parks and nature reserves which you visit---all
profits from this tour go to the parks and to local environmental groups!<P>


Dates for the tour are from July 16 to August 7.  Includes a minimum of 7 days on park-owned boats, plying
the waves of this, the Sacred Sea of Siberia.  (Tour is led by <A HREF="baikal.html">Baikal Watch</A>
Director Gary Cook and famed photographer Boyd Norton.  Call <B>Oceanic Society Expeditions</B> at USA
415-441-1106 to receive more information, or to make reservations---we are limited to 15 participants, so
don't hesitate too long!)<P>

