<P><A HREF="stateguide.html">State-by-State Guide to Ecological Paper Retailers,
Printers, and Manufacturers</A></P>

<H1>&nbsp;</H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="image6.gif" WIDTH="168" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="2"
HEIGHT="36" NATURALSIZEFLAG="2"></H1>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>ECOLOGICAL PAPER RESOURCES:</H2>

<P><BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Major Ecological Paper Retailers</H3>

<UL>
  <LI><B>Arbour</B>: Sells recycled paper office supplies and carries a selection
  of hemp and kenaf paper. Contact Sean Twomey at (613) 567-3168 (Ontario,
  Canada).
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/GreenMarket/COMPANIES/Dance/index.html"><B>Dancing
  Tree</B></A>: Offers kenaf papers and has an excellent selection of recycled
  papers for printing and writing. Contact Josh Grossman at (510) 486-1616
  (CA).
  <LI><B>Earth Care Products</B>: Sells home and office supplies, carries
  other forest friendly products as well, (800) 762-7325, (CA).
  <LI><A HREF="http://ecolution.com/"><B>Ecolution</B></A>: Sells high quality
  hemp papers made in Eastern Europe. Contact Eric at (703) 207-9001 (VA).
  <LI><B>Friendly Chameleon, The</B>: Hemp paper, stationary, and office
  supplies, (215) 487-3317 (PA).
  <LI><B>Living Tree Paper</B>: Agricultural-residue, hemp, and post-consumer
  recycled paper blend, (503) 342-2974 (OR).
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.ganet.net/~ps2/hemp.html"><B>Ohio Hempery</B></A>:
  Sells hemp papers and Tradition Bond papers. Contact 800-Buy-Hemp (OH).
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.pcw100.com/"><B>PCW100</B></A>: Printer and paper
  vendor carrying a variety of tree-free (kenaf, hemp, cotton, and reclaimed
  fabric) and 100% post-consumer recycled papers. Contact Greg Barber at
  (800) PCW-3117.
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.teleport.com/~ptree/"><B>PeaceTree</B></A>: Environmental
  printers offering recycled and tree-free papers, (503) 233-5821 (OR).
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.envirolink.org/treeco/"><B>Treeco</B></A>: Sells
  office supplies, kenaf, hemp, and many different types of recycled papers
  for special projects and office needs. Contact Janet Harold (310) 399-TREE
  (CA).
</UL>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Manufacturers / Wholesale Distributors (large orders)</H3>

<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="http://agripulp.com/"><B>Arbokem Canada</B></A>: Manufactures
  and sells a 50% wheat straw, 50% post-consumer waste paper (PCW) blend.
  One case minimum order. Contact Al Wong at (604) 322-1317 (Brit. Col.,
  Canada).
  <LI><B>Fox River: </B>First large paper company to produce a tree-free
  paper line. Paper is made from Asian bamboo and is elemental chlorine-free
  bleached (not the best, but an excellent start. Contact Fox River at (800)
  558-8327.
  <LI><B>Green Earth Office Supply</B>: Tree-free stationery and printing
  papers bleached totally-chlorine-free, (800) 327-8449 (CA).
  <LI><B>Green Field Paper Co.</B>: Organic cotton printing/writing paper
  and stationery, and other eco-paper products, (619) 338-9432 (CA).
  <LI><B>Tree Free Eco Paper</B>: sells hemp and agricultural waste (straw)
  residue papers. Contact David Potter at (800) 775-0225 (OR).
  <LI><B>Vision Paper Co.</B>: Makes and sells kenaf papers in different
  sizes and weights, to retailers, printers, publishers. Vision Paper supplies
  the kenaf for the <I>Earth Island Journal.</I> One case minimum order (10
  reams). Contact Lynn at (505) 294-0293 (NM).
</UL>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Printing Firms with Experience Using Ecological Papers</H3>

<UL>
  <LI><B>Alonzo Printing</B>: Prints Earth Island Journal on tree-free paper.
  Contact Bob Alonzo at (510) 293-0522 (CA).
  <LI><B>Anderson Lithographic</B>: Large printing firm that uses kenaf for
  clients such as the Gap and Apple. Contact Bob Lewis at (415) 233-2333
  (CA).
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/GreenMarket/COMPANIES/Dance/index.html"><B>Dancing
  Tree</B></A>: Offers kenaf papers and has an excellent selection of recycled
  papers for printing and writing, (510) 486-1616 (CA).
  <LI><B>Ecoprint</B>: Printer that uses vegetable-based inks and 100% post-consumer
  waste (PCW) and tree-free papers bleached totally-chlorine-free (TCF),
  (301) 585-7077 (MD).
  <LI><B>George Rice and Sons</B>: Leading printer for advanced color-printing
  projects, (415) 468-0900 (CA).
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.pcw100.com/"><B>PCW100</B></A>: Printer and paper
  vendor carrying a variety of tree-free (kenaf, hemp, cotton, and reclaimed
  fabric) and 100% post-consumer recycled papers. Contact Greg Barber at
  (800) PCW-3117.
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.teleport.com/~ptree/"><B>PeaceTree</B></A>: Environmental
  printers offering recycled and tree-free papers, (503) 233-5821 (OR).
  <LI><B>Somerset</B>: Large-scale printers using agricultural residue and
  kenaf paper, (800) 966-8545 (CA).
  <LI><B>Ventura Printing</B>: Large scale printers using agricultural waste
  paper for companies such as Patagonia (CA).
</UL>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><BR>
Publishing Companies Using Ecological Papers</H3>

<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.harpercollins.com/"><B>Harper Collins</B></A>:
  Printed David Brower's <I>Let the Mountains Talk, Let the Rivers Run</I>
  on kenaf paper. Phone (415) 477-4400 (San Francisco, CA).
  <LI><B>H.E.M.P.</B>: Printed Jack Herer's The Emperor Wears No Clothes
  on hemp, (707) 887-7508 (Lafayette, CA).
  <LI><B>Sixth Street Press</B>: Printed Sharon Young's Abundant Harvest
  on kenaf, (209) 229-4282 (Fresno, CA).
</UL>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Industry Associations</H3>

<UL>
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.tappi.org/"><B>TAPPI</B></A>: International paper
  pulping association offering information on technical aspects of nonwood
  paper making, (770) 446-1400 (GA).
  <LI><B>International Kenaf Association</B>: Kenaf industry association,
  (903) 367-7216 (TX).
  <LI><B>International Hemp Association</B>: Hemp industry association, (011)
  31-618-5591 (Amsterdam, The Netherlands).
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.hempworld.com/"><B>Hempworld</B></A>: International
  hemp journal, (707) 887-7508.
</UL>

<P><BR>
<B><HR ALIGN=LEFT></B></P>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><BR>
The Absolute Best Recycled Papers<BR>
(50% minimum post-consumer content)</H3>

<UL>
  <LI><B>Cross Pointe</B>: Genesis, 100% PCW, deinked, PCF, uncoated.
  <LI><B>Domtar</B>: Sandpiper, 100% PCW, non-deinked, Process-Chlorine-Free
  (PCF), and uncoated (mill certified and verified).
  <LI><B>International Paper</B>: Hammermill, Unity DP, 100% de-inked old
  newspapers and magazines. Contains a minimum of 50% Post-Consumer-Waste
  (PCW).
  <LI><B>James River</B>: Graphika, 100% recycled (60% PCW), non-deinked
  (mill verified). Eureka 100, 100% PCW.
  <LI><B>Mohawk</B>: Vellum, 100% PCW, non-deinked, PCF, uncoated (not mill
  verified).
  <LI><B>Recyconomic</B>: Steinbeiss paper from Europe, 50-90% PCW, and PCF
  (pre-consumer fiber).
  <LI><B>Simpson</B>: Quest, 100% PCW, non-deinked, uncoated.
  <LI><B>Springhill</B>: Incentive, 100% recycled (50% PCW). Includes mill
  broke and is deinked (mill verified).
</UL>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Suppliers</H3>

<UL>
  <LI><B>American Paper Sales</B>: (212) 889-3001; Chlorine Free - Domestic
  and imported.
  <LI><B>Arbour</B>: Sells recycled paper office supplies and carries a selection
  of hemp and kenaf paper. Contact Sean Twomey at (613) 567-3168, (Ontario,
  Canada).
  <LI><B>Atlantic Recycled Paper Co.</B>: (800) 775-0225; Recycled - Imported
  and domestic.
  <LI><B>Classen Papertronics</B>: (214) 490-5128; Imported, coated chlorine-free.
  <LI><B>Cross Pointe</B>: (800) 845-4500; full line of recycled papers.
  <LI><B>Dancing Tree</B>: (510) 486-1616; wide selection of recycled papers
  from different companies.
  <LI><B>Domtar</B>: (800) 267-3060; Sandpiper line.
  <LI><B>Earth Care Products</B>: Sells home and office supplies, carries
  other forest friendly products as well, (800) 762-7325 (CA).
  <LI><B>Hayden and Cary &amp;King</B>: (203) 656-3111; recycled and TCF
  papers.
  <LI><B>James River</B>: (510) 874-3600; Eureka 100 - Graphika.
  <LI><B>MoDo Cell Inc.</B>: (203) 854-9447; uncoated, TCF papers.
  <LI><B>Mohawk Paper</B>: (800) 543-4776;Vellum line.
  <LI><B>Niagara</B>: (800) 826-043; TCF and 30% PCW.
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.pcw100.com/"><B>PCW100</B></A>: (800) PCW-3117;
  Printer and paper vendor carrying a variety of 100% post-consumer recycled
  papers.
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.teleport.com/~ptree/"><B>PeaceTree</B></A>: (503)
  233-5821; Environmental printer and paper supplier.
  <LI><B>Simpson</B>: (415) 358-9970; Quest line.
  <LI><A HREF="http://www.envirolink.org/treeco/"><B>Treeco</B></A>: Sells
  office supplies, recycled papers for special projects and office needs,
  (310) 399-TREE (CA).
</UL>

