<H1><CENTER><BR>
<FONT SIZE = 10><A HREF="titt.html">NO DEPOSIT...</A></FONT><BR>
<IMG SRC="nytmc.jpg" WIDTH="125" HEIGHT="175" ALIGN=
middle NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="1"><IMG SRC="nytmc2.jpg"
WIDTH="125" HEIGHT="175" ALIGN=middle NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="1"><IMG SRC=
"nytmc4.jpg" WIDTH="125" HEIGHT="175" ALIGN=middle
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="1"></CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER>One for the Scrap Heap: <I>The New York Times Magazine</I> Slips
Up On Recycling</CENTER>
<H1><CENTER><FONT SIZE = 10><A HREF="titt.html">NO RETURN</A></FONT><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="image6.gif" WIDTH="239" HEIGHT="50" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"0" BORDER="2"><BR>
<FONT SIZE = 8>vs.</FONT><BR>
<IMG SRC="nyt_logo.gif" WIDTH="301" HEIGHT="54" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"1" BORDER="1"> </CENTER>
</H1>
<H1><FONT SIZE = 6></H1>
<H1><CENTER>Earth Island Institute's <FONT COLOR = GREEN><FONT SIZE = 6>ReThink Paper</FONT>
<FONT COLOR = BLACK><FONT SIZE = 6>
project challenges the editors of <I>The NY Times Magazine</I> to explain
how they could let John Tierney's execrable reporting on recycling pass
muster at the nation's newspaper of record.</FONT><BR>
</CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER><FONT SIZE = 3><FONT COLOR = BLACK>For more information, contact Emily Miggins, Brian West, or Mark Mardon at ReThink
Paper<BR><B>Phone:</B> (415) 788-3666 / <B>E-mail:</B> rtp@igc.apc.org / <B>Web:</B> 
www.earthisland.orgrtp.html
</CENTER><BR>
<HR></CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3><CENTER><IMG SRC="scoop.gif" WIDTH="297" HEIGHT="53" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3" ALIGN=bottom></CENTER>
</H3>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><CENTER><A HREF="rtp.html">ReThink Paper Home Page</A> <BR>
<A HREF="overview.html">Campaign Overview</A> | <A HREF="ffpcamp.html">The
main components of ReThink Paper</A> <BR>
<A HREF="sus.paper.html">The Sustainable Paper Cycle: A Vision for the future</A>
<BR>
The Plain Pulp Facts: <A HREF="paperstats1.html">Volume 1</A> | <A HREF="woodfact.html">Wood
Consumption Facts </A><BR>
<A HREF="tfpdef.html">Tree-free fibers and paper </A>| <A HREF="ecosources.html">Ecological
paper suppliers and resources </A><BR>
