<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="junkmail2.gif">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="stopjunk.gif" WIDTH="302" HEIGHT="59" BORDER=
"1" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></H1>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#330099" SIZE=+2>An Uncluttered Guide to Reducing
Pesky Junkmail</FONT></H3>

<H5 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#E62802" SIZE=+0>printed on 100% virtual junkmail
paper</FONT></H5>

<H5 ALIGN=CENTER><HR WIDTH="67%"></H5>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#BF0344" SIZE=+4>T</FONT><FONT COLOR="#BF0344"
 SIZE=+3>he </FONT><FONT COLOR="#BF0344" SIZE=+4>S</FONT><FONT COLOR="#BF0344"
 SIZE=+3>olid-</FONT><FONT COLOR="#BF0344" SIZE=+4>W</FONT><FONT COLOR="#BF0344"
 SIZE=+3>aste </FONT><FONT COLOR="#BF0344" SIZE=+4>P</FONT><FONT COLOR="#BF0344"
 SIZE=+3>roblem</FONT></H2>

<UL>
  <LI><B><FONT COLOR="#2B7F16" SIZE=+1>In 1988 the United States produced
  180 million tons of solid waste, that is an average of 4 lbs. a day per
  person. This figure is projected to double by the year 2010</FONT><FONT
   COLOR="#306632" SIZE=+1>.</FONT><FONT COLOR="#FFD303" SIZE=+1> <BR>
  <BR>
  </FONT></B>
  <LI><B><FONT COLOR="#9D012F" SIZE=+1>Approximately 40% of this solid mass
  that comprises our landfills is paper and paperboard waste. It will make
  up at least 48% of the landfill mass by the year 2010. <BR>
  <BR>
  </FONT></B>
  <LI><B><FONT COLOR="#663300" SIZE=+1>In 1988, we only recycled approximately
  13% of the total waste generated in the US. Nearly 14 % was combusted (incinerated)
  while the remaining 73% went to landfills. Clearly, this cannot be sustained.<BR>
  <BR>
  </FONT></B>
  <LI><B><FONT COLOR="#035EAD" SIZE=+1>We are literally running out of space
  to fill by discarding waste that could easily be recycled. Because many
  landfills have reached their capacity and pose many environmental risks,
  only 6,000 of the 20,000 landfills operating in 1978 remained open in 1990
  - a 70% closure rate over twelve years.</FONT></B>
  <LI>&nbsp;
</UL>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <H2 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#BF0344" SIZE=+4>Take Action!</FONT></H2>
  <H5><IMG SRC="junk.gif" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" BORDER="1"><FONT SIZE=+1>Return solicitations that include a postage
  paid reply envelope; include a note requesting that you be removed from
  the mailing list.</FONT><FONT SIZE=+0></FONT></H5>
  <H5><FONT SIZE=+0><BR>
  <IMG SRC="junk.gif" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" BORDER="1"></FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>Call the toll-free number of companies
  sending you unwanted mail, and request that your name and address be removed
  from their database. <BR>
  </FONT><FONT SIZE=+0><BR>
  <IMG SRC="junk.gif" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" BORDER="1"></FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>Write to the Direct Marketing Association
  (DMA) to have your name removed from their database: DMA Mail Preference
  Service, P.O. Box 9008, Farmingdale, NY 11735. Be sure to include all names
  and addresses under which you receive unwanted mail.<BR>
  </FONT><FONT SIZE=+0><BR>
  <IMG SRC="junk.gif" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" BORDER="1"></FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>Each time you request a catalog or
  make a mail order purchase, request that your name not be sold or traded
  to other mailers.<BR>
  </FONT><FONT SIZE=+0><BR>
  <IMG SRC="junk.gif" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" BORDER="1"></FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>Find a recylcing program that accepts
  junk mail under the &quot;mixed- paper&quot; category.<BR>
  </FONT><FONT SIZE=+0></FONT></H5>
  <H5><FONT SIZE=+0><BR>
  <IMG SRC="junk.gif" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" BORDER="1"></FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>Make your own recycled paper at home
  by cutting junk mail into small shreds, soaking in warm water (1 hour -
  stir occasionaly) and spreading out on a flat, fine-holed wire-mesh screen.
  Add flowers, grass etc. to add color and texture.</FONT><FONT SIZE=+0><BR>
  <BR>
  <IMG SRC="junk.gif" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" BORDER="1"></FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>Ship your third class mail by the boxful,
  (no magazines or newsprint please!) to: FoundStuff Paper Works, 744 G Street
  #201, San Diego, CA 92101 - where it will be recycled in a first class
  way as handmade stationery (This web page is printed on scanned - virtual
  junk mail stationary from Found Stuff) - To find out more about this special
  company and its products, call (619) 338-9432</FONT></H5>
  
  <P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <H3 ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="scoop.gif" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="43" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
  "3" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></H3>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="rtp.html">ReThink Paper Home Page</A> <BR>
    <A HREF="overview.html">Campaign Overview</A> | <A HREF="ffpcamp.html">The
    main components of ReThink Paper</A> <BR>
    <A HREF="sus.paper.html">The Sustainable Paper Cycle: A Vision for the
    future</A> <BR>
    The Plain Pulp Facts: <A HREF="paperstats1.html">Volume 1</A> | <A HREF=
    "woodfact.html">Wood Consumption Facts </A><BR>
    <A HREF="tfpdef.html">Tree-free fibers and paper </A>| <A HREF="ecosources.html">Ecological
    paper suppliers and resources </A><BR>
    Tree-free fibers for papermaking: <A HREF="kenaf.html">Kenaf</A>; <A HREF=
    "hemp.html">Hemp</A> <BR>
    <A HREF="wycd.html">What you can do to &quot;ReThink Paper&quot;</A> |
    <A HREF="eiiffpp.html">Earth Island Journal</A></P>
