  <TITLE>What You Can Do</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="crumple.gif" LINK="#75480a" VLINK="#015800">

<H1>&nbsp;</H1>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#000000" SIZE=+2>What </FONT><B><FONT COLOR="#330099"
 SIZE=+2>You</FONT><FONT COLOR="#BF0344" SIZE=+2> </FONT></B><FONT COLOR="#000000"
 SIZE=+2>Can Do To . . .</FONT><FONT COLOR="#0000FF" SIZE=+2> </FONT></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B><I><FONT COLOR="#0000FF" SIZE=+4>ReThink Paper</FONT></I></B></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B><I><FONT COLOR="#0000FF" SIZE=+4></FONT></I></B>&nbsp;</P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
  <BLOCKQUOTE>
    <P ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="450" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="4" CELLPADDING=
    "4">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#ffff00">    <P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=+1>Become a member of <B>ReThink Paper</B>.
    By doing so, you will directly support RTP's ongoing efforts to transform
    the pulp-and-paper industry. With your $25 membership you will receive
    a one-year subscription to the award winning <I>Earth Island Journal </I>,
    printed on 100% tree-free paper. <B>Call (415) 788-3666</B> for more information
    on joining RTP. </FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#000fff">    <P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" SIZE=+1>Choose tree-free or
    50-100% post-consumer paper. Examine the content of the paper you buy.
    Avoid recycled paper whose content is made up of pre-consumer and virgin-wood
    fibers.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#ffff00">    <P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=+1>Reinforce recycling in your own home
    and business. Make sure you are recycling all paper and products made from
    paper.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#000fff">    <P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" SIZE=+1>Print your documents
    on both sides to save $$$ and trees.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#ffff00">    <P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;<FONT SIZE=+1>Beware that all paper identified as
    &quot;recycled&quot; may not be ecologically sound. Most papers with the
    &quot;recycled&quot; label have a very small percentage of recycled fiber
    content mixed with a high percentage of virgin pulp fiber.</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%" BGCOLOR="#000fff">    <P ALIGN=CENTER>&nbsp;<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" SIZE=+1>Share this information
    with friends!</FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
</P>
  </BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

