<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Earth Island Journal:100% tree-free</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#75480a" VLINK="#015800">
<H1>Earth Island Journal:100% tree-free since '94<HR></H1>
During the past two years Earth Island Institute has explored and advocated
the use of <A HREF="tffibp.html">tree-free</A> fibers for <A HREF="tfpdef.html">paper</A>
production. Earth Island's efforts began with the publication of a series
of articles in its quarterly magazine, Earth Island Journal, investigating
the current paper industry and the potential for change. In 1994, putting
words into action, Earth Island Journal published the first 100 percent
tree-free magazine in the US using paper made from the kenaf plant. <BR>
<BR>
Earth Island now proposes to move beyond the demonstration phase and initiate
a formal ReThink Paper campaign. We are able to begin this campaign with
the generous and enthusiastic support and funding of the Turner Foundation,
based in Atlanta, and the Columbia Foundation located here in San Francisco.<BR>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3><CENTER><IMG SRC="scoop.gif" WIDTH="172" HEIGHT="43" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3" ALIGN=bottom></CENTER>
