<html>







<head>



<title>Costa Rica Trip</title>



</head>







<body>







<h1 align=center>Costa Rica Eco-Service Project</h1>



<h3 align=center>



<i>Experience small village lifestyle while assisting with community service and conservation projects.</i>



</h3>







<img SRC="hola1.gif" align=left>







<p>The Costa Rica Eco-Service project is a 2-1/2 week project working with rainforest communities who are 



struggling to keep themselves going without damaging their environment. Volunteers stay one week



with each of two different Costa Rican communities, participating in their efforts to both survive and sustain, 



and experiencing the day-to-day life of the people.







<p>Volunteers will depart the U.S. and arrive in the Costa Rican capital of San Jose.  The following morning, 



the group will be driven through lush countryside to the beautiful Monteverde rainforest preserve.  After a 



brief orientation and guided tour of the rainforest provided by the Monteverde Conservation League, we 



will travel to the small developing community of San Gerardo located in the heart of the International 



Children's Rainforest.  Here we will stay for six days in the eco-lodge facilities and assist the members of 



the community in their project of creating and developing a center for scientific research and eco tourism.  



The group will assist with activities such as gardening, construction, and trail maintenance.







<p>For the second half of the trip, the group will travel to Buen Amigo, a small farming community working to 



become self sustainable.  We will stay either in the new eco-lodge dormitory or in the homes of hospitable 



local families.  The work done in Buen Amigo is chosen by the community, based on their needs at the time.  



Such activities could include reforestation, picking coffee, or working on the eco-lodge.  After six days in 



Buen Amigo, we will travel to La Fortuna, a resort town at the foot of the spectacular Arenal Volcano.  



There the group will enjoy relaxing in the famous hot springs and admiring the amazing view of the volcano.  



Finally, we return to San Jose where we will enjoy a goodbye banquet dinner.  The following morning we 



will return to the United States, satisfied by our contribution to communities of the Costa Rican rainforest.



<p>







<hr>







<h3>Costa Rica Project News</h3>







<p>The people of the rainforest communities of Costa Rica are being torn by two opposing forces: protecting their 



environment and feeding their families. The community of San Gerardo, for example, live s on land that is 



environmentally protected by the government. This makes it almost impossible to grow enough food using



traditional methods, so almost all of the people of San Gerardo have moved away. The Monteverde Conservation 



League, a Costa Rican environmental organization, had an idea. They began building a research station for 



scientific study of the rainforest. By increasing opportunitie s for employment and education, they hope to



encourage the people of the community to return to the lands they once called home, where they can both feed 



their families and protect their ecosystem.







<p>In Other News...







<p>We recently heard from Paul Englander, a returned GSC volunteer from our December '95 Costa Rica project. He 



said he liked it there so much, he wants to go back! We are setting up a long-term placement for him at Monteverde, 



and he should be there by the middle of this summer.  Welcome back Paul! And, hasta luego!







<p>"Working as a team in a group of volunteers/ local people helping to improve the community was what I wanted to 



do... This was the perfect way to give something back."







<p>Paul Englander, 



<br>Once and future GSC volunteer







<hr>







<h3>Project Dates and Costs:</h3>



<ul>



<li>1996: August 9 - 25,   December 27 - January 12 



<li>1997: March 7-23, June 13-29, August 1-18, November 7-24



<li>$1495 land costs



</ul><p>







<hr>







