<html>







<head>



<title>Thailand trip</title>



</head>







<body>







<h1 align=center>Thailand English Instruction Project</h1>



<h3 align=center>



<i>Community service and cultural exchange with people from the "Land of Smiles".</i>



</h3>







<img SRC="savat2.gif" align=left>







<p>Like many global citizens, Thais are eager to learn English as a way to communicate with foreigners 



and as an entry into the international marketplace.  In rural Thailand, schools often lack the resources 



to hire native speakers or acquire further training for their present teachers.  GSC collaborates with these 



schools, providing volunteers to teach language and cross-cultural awareness in small villages.  For many 



Thai students, this is their first opportunity to meet and practice with a native English speaker.     







<p>The group will depart on a Saturday, and arrive in Bangkok the following day. After spending Monday resting 



up and sightseeing in Bangkok, we will depart the next morning for the Chiang Mai region of northern 



Thailand.  Our destination will be a local village set among the rolling green mountains of this region.  Here 



the group will be teaching English in local schools and also working with local community leaders and villagers, 



assisting with community projects. Typical projects include assisting in the construction of a women's cooperative 



building, helping with gardening projects, or working on a potable water system.<p>







<p>Participants will be housed in homes of the villagers and will join these families for some meals.  The homes are 



traditional wooden houses and the meals will consist of simple, delicious Thai fare.  You may have to do without



conveniences such as Western toilets and electricity during your stay.  At the same time, you will be welcomed into 



the homes of undoubtedly some of the friendliest people in the world who are always eager to offer farangs



(foreigners) warm hospitality.  Although our group will be accompanied by a Thai-speaking guide, you will enjoy 



learning new ways of communicating across culture and language differences.







<p>During our stay in the village, the group will spend several days exploring the Chiang Mai region, including a nearby 



national park.  We depart for Bangkok on the final Thursday.  On Friday and Saturday we spend time visiting the



Bangkok area, including local Buddhist wats (monasteries), the floating markets and other highlights.  We will depart 



Bangkok on Saturday, and arrive in San Francisco on Sunday.<p>







<hr>







<h3>Thailand Project News</h3>







<p>Thailand project participants live and work in the rustic villages of the beautiful Lamphun Province.  Here, we will 



experience the exceptional Thai warmth and hospitality while staying with a local family, sharing meals and activities 



throughout our stay. Days will be spent teaching at a nearby school or Buddhist monastery.  Thai youth are enthusiastic 



and affectionate students and will be very excited to have a foreign teacher.  Weekends will be free for sightseeing and 



exploring the region.  Past participants have traveled to nearby Chiang Mai or hired a guide for a trek into the



mountains to visit the indigenous hilltribe peoples.







<p>In Other News...







<p>Assisting with these efforts is GSC's new in-country coordinator, Lisa Patlis.  Lisa, who participated in our August 



1994 Kenya Biointensive project, recently set up house in Bangkok with her husband and acts as a local representative 



for GSC.  She coordinates with the growing number of schools that have expressed interest in having GSC volunteers 



teach English to their students.  In addition, she is establishing connections with other community development



projects in which GSC volunteers may participate.  Lisa has an MA in public administration and, before moving to 



Thailand, worked with HUD in Washington D.C..











<HR>







<h3>Project Dates and Costs:</h3>



<li>1996: November 2 - 24



<li>1997: January 25 - February 16, June 21 - July 13, November 1 - 23



<li>$1695 land cost



</ul><p>







