<head>



<title>How to register for a trip</title>



</head>







<body>







<H2>HOW TO REGISTER FOR A GSC VOLUNTEER PROJECT TRIP</H2>







Since Global Service Corps is interested in giving as many people as possible 



the opportunity to learn about our global challenges while assisting on a 



sustainable development project, we do not require a specific technical 



expertise or educational background.  However, there are two general 



requirements which all participants must meet:<p>







<OL>



<LI>You must be committed to participating on a trip which has as its primary 



purposes service and learning.  GSC project trips are not just an alternative, 



&quot;interesting&quot; vacation.  



<LI>You must be willing to be flexible and open to a less structured and more 



&quot;laid back&quot; environment. While citizens of developed 



countries are usually accomplishment-oriented and time-structured, citizens of 



developing countries are more often interested in the experience of events and 



relationships.  This means that activities may not  always take place as 



originally planned or &quot;on time.&quot;  Flexibility, good humor and 



a willingness to experience life through another perspective are all 



prerequisites to participation.



</OL><p>











<B>There are two ways to register for a GSC Volunteer Project Trip:</B><p>







<OL>



<LI>If you have already become a Global Service Corps Supporter 



(see <A HREF="invol.html">How you can be involved</A>), 



merely notify the GSC office which project trip you wish to participate 



in and you will be sent materials to compete your application process. These 



will include an application and release form, information about travel and 



health insurance, details regarding the project setting, and a volunteer 



background and information form.  You will later receive additional information 



including a day by day itinerary, a map of the host country, health 



precautions, a clothing and equipment list, information on discount airfares, 



and helpful words and phrases in the local language.







<BR>



<li>If you are not a Global Service Corps Supporter, send the $35 registration 



fee to the GSC office (Global Service Corps Volunteers, 



300 Broadway, Suite 38, San Francisco, CA 94133-3312, USA. 



Checks should be made out to Global Service Corps/Earth Island Institute)



<BR>



along with the following information:



<BR>







<UL>



<LI>Name (as it appears on your passport)



<LI>Address



<LI>Telephone numbers (home, office and fax)



<LI>Which project trip you wish to participate in



</UL>







</OL><p>







You will then be sent materials to complete your application.  After this first step of the application process 



is completed, you will be asked to submit a $500 deposit with the remainder of the project trip fee due 



45 days before departure.<p>







