<TITLE>Ocean Alert - Summer/Fall 1995</TITLE>

<H1>Ocean Alert - Summer/Fall 1995</H1>

<B>Campaign Mission: </B><I>Earth Island Institute's (EII) International 
Marine Mammal Project (IMMP) works to make oceans safe for marine mammals 
worldwide. We strive to eliminate dolphin mortality caused by the 
international tuna fishing industry, to end the use of driftnets, and to 
stop tuna purse-seine fishers from encircling dolphins in their nets. In 
addition, we aim to stop the resumption of commercial whaling worldwide 
and to promote sustainable fishing.</I>
<P>

<IMG SRC="dolphin.gif" 
ALIGN=Right 
VSPACE=1 
HSPACE=1>

<H2>Table of Contents: </H2>

<OL>
<A HREF="oasf9501.html">    <LI> A Message from David Phillips</A>
<P>
<A HREF="oasf9502.html">     <LI> The Norwegian Whaling Scandal</A>
<P>
<A HREF="oasf9503.html">     <LI> Keiko to Move to Oregon</A>
<P>
<A HREF="oasf9504.html">     <LI> The Dolphin-Safe Tuna Anniversary</A> 
<P>
<A HREF="oasf9505.html">     <LI> Saving Seals in San Francisco Bay</A>
<P>
<A HREF="oasf9506.html">     <LI> Monitor Highlight</A>
<P>
<A HREF="oasf9507.html">     <LI> Whales Alive Project Report</A>
<P>
<A HREF="oasf9508.html">     <LI> What You Can Do</A>
<P>
<A HREF="oasf9509.html">     <LI> International Marine Mammal Project Staff</A>
