<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Adopt-a-Watershed</TITLE></HEAD> 
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Adopt-A-Watershed in the Southern Rockies!</H2><BODY> 
The Southern Rockies Restoration Project is working to assist citizens in restoring damaged ecosystems by organizing watershed councils, and providing technical assistance for restoration projects throughout the region.  You can become involved by participating in our 'Adopt-A-Watershed' program.  If you have a favorite stream or care about a special wild place somewhere in the Southern Rockies region of western Colorado or Northern New Mexico, your financial and/or time commitment can go a long way toward rekindling the wild character of the land.<P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><B>By adopting a watershed, you will:</B>

<!-- List Tag --><UL TYPE=disc>
<LI>Become eligible to serve on that watershed's Council<BR>
<LI>Support an assessment of restoration needs in that watershed<BR>
<LI>Be informed of opportunities to conduct restoration field work<BR>
<LI>Receive a one-year subscription to <I>Earth Island Journal,</I> an award-winning quarterly environmental  magazine
</UL><P>
</P>
Adoption contributions are $25 or more for individuals, and $40 or more for businesses.  <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="adopt2.html">Click here</A> for a list of watersheds and to submit an adoption form.<BR>
<BR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><BLOCKQUOTE><CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="overview.html">Project Overview</A> | <!-- Link Tag --><!--A HREF="region.html">The Southern Rockies Ecoregion</A></CENTER>
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><!--A HREF="assess.html">Regional Watershed Assessment</A> | <!-- Link Tag --><!--A HREF="councils.html">Watershed Councils</A></CENTER>
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag --></CENTER>
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag --><!--A HREF="councils.html">Join the Southern Rockies Restoration Project</A></CENTER><center><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="srrp.html">Back to SRRP home page</center></A></BLOCKQUOTE></P>
</BODY>

